					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10420833#post-4235630</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10420833/scp-3683#post-4235630</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 01 May 2019 20:46:16 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Hawkin</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1529032</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Well,&nbsp;if&nbsp;we're&nbsp;going&nbsp;to&nbsp;go&nbsp;all&nbsp;MTG&nbsp;on&nbsp;it...</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">...here's&nbsp;a&nbsp;thing.</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>Recombinant Pigeon - 3BluBlu</p> <p>Creature - Bird</p> <p>2/2</p> <p>Flying</p> <p>Whenever you play a Bird with a keyword ability, you may tap Recombinant Pigeon. If you do, Recombinant Pigeon gains that keyword ability.</p> <p>[TAP]2Blu - Put a +1/+1 counter on Recombinant Pigeon.</p> <p>When Recombinant Pigeon dies, put X 1/1 blue Pigeon creatures with flying into play under your control, where X is the number of +1/+1 counters on Recombinant Pigeon.</p> <p>Sacrifice X Pigeons - Return Recombinant Pigeon from your graveyard to play with X - 2 +1/+1 counters on it.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>Now I want a SCP-based MTG block.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
